==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: irones
<hw>i"rones</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A fragrant liquid substance, a mixture of several isomers of the
formula <chform>C14H22O</chform>, forming the essence of the violet
fragrance, commonly isolated from orris oil or from the rhizomes of
Iris. The main ingredient in violets is <stype>⟦alpha⟧-irone</stype>,
which occurs as both cis and trans stereoisomers. Called also
<altname>6-methylionone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ironer</ent>⟦br⟧
